   <mods:abstract>Contains commentaries, notes, and quotations on questions of foreign
            policy; notes on an opinion of John Jay's character and the reasons he was selected as
            President of the Continental Congress. MS [transcripts].Includes: n.d. [1778?],
            Reflections on the question of whether the United States should be influenced by the
            spirit of conquest; December [1778?], Conrad Gerard's opinion on the Floridas; 2
            December [1778?], A Character of John Jay by Conrad Gerard; 25 December 1778, Proposal
            of a Truce between England and the United States, made to Gerard (extract); 21 October
            1780, New Instructions to John Jay [from Marbois] (with notes); 17 July 1783, John Jay
            to Gouverneur Morris (extract, with notes).</mods:abstract>
